'''大卫·麦克布莱德'''（{{Lang|en|David William McBride}}，{{bd|1963年|}}）是一位澳大利亚籍[[吹哨人|吹哨人]]。'''麦克布莱德'''揭露了[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]特种部队士兵在驻阿富汗期间杀害多名平民，并因此遭到澳大利亚司法部门以未经授权披露信息、违反澳大利亚国防法等五项罪名指控<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=就在澳总理对中国狂怒时，这个曝光澳军暴行的人却危险了|url=https://world.huanqiu.com/article/40uopRlX6Xl|accessdate=2020-12-01|author=|date=2020-12-01|format=|publisher=环球网|language=zh|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201213030514/https://world.huanqiu.com/article/40uopRlX6Xl|archivedate=2020-12-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>，如果罪名成立，大卫或将面临五十年的监禁。

== 生平 ==
先后就读于[[悉尼大學|悉尼大学]]、[[牛津大学|牛津大学]]<ref name="Knaus">{{cite news|last1=Knaus|first1=Christopher|title=Whistleblower charged with exposing alleged military misconduct 'not afraid to go to jail'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/mar/07/whistleblower-charged-with-exposing-alleged-military-misconduct-not-afraid-to-go-to-jail|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|quote=David McBride, 55, is facing five charges...|date=7 March 2019|accessdate=2020-12-01|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127110238/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/mar/07/whistleblower-charged-with-exposing-alleged-military-misconduct-not-afraid-to-go-to-jail|dead-url=no}}</ref>，其在英国留学期间加入[[英軍|英军]]，曾获得[[英国陆军|英国陆军]]少校军衔<ref name="Wroe">{{cite news|last1=Wroe|first1=David|title='What I've done makes sense to me': The complicated, colourful life of David McBride|url=https://www.smh.com.au/politics/federal/what-i-ve-done-makes-sense-to-me-the-complicated-colourful-life-of-david-mcbride-20190621-p5204h.html|accessdate=19 November 2020|work=[[The_Sydney_Morning_Herald|The Sydney Morning Herald]]|date=22 June 2019|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107231941/https://www.smh.com.au/politics/federal/what-i-ve-done-makes-sense-to-me-the-complicated-colourful-life-of-david-mcbride-20190621-p5204h.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

返回[[悉尼|悉尼]]的麦克布莱德也找了几份工作，最终他去应聘进入[[澳大利亚国防军|澳大利亚国防军]]，成为一位军事律师<ref name="Wroe" />，并于2011年、2013年两次随军前往阿富汗<ref name=":0" /><ref name="Wroe" /><ref name="Xenophon">{{Cite web|title=If moral courage matters, this whistleblower needs defending|url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/if-moral-courage-matters-this-whistleblower-needs-defending-20201116-p56ey4.html|date=2020-11-17|last=Xenophon|first=Nick|access-date=2020-11-19|website=The Age|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107231944/https://www.theage.com.au/national/if-moral-courage-matters-this-whistleblower-needs-defending-20201116-p56ey4.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{cite news|title='It is an abomination': Nick Xenophon condemns national security laws and treatment of whistleblowers|first1=Paul|last1=Johnson|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-06-23/nick-xenophon-afghan-files-david-mcbride-witness-j-whistleblower/12382154|accessdate=19 November 2020|publisher=ABC|date=22 June 2020|archive-date=2021-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210303044222/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-06-23/nick-xenophon-afghan-files-david-mcbride-witness-j-whistleblower/12382154|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其从军期间发现、并搜集调查了自2014年到2016年间，[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]士兵在[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]涉嫌[[战争罪|战争罪]]行的信息。2017年，麦克布莱德因为患有[[PTSD|创伤应激后遗症]]而不得不退役<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />。他对澳大利亚军队在阿富汗犯下的战争罪提出了内部指控，将其调查报告提供给了[[澳大利亚广播公司|澳大利亚广播公司]]的记者丹·奥克斯。同年7月，[[澳大利亚广播公司|澳大利亚广播公司]]将澳大利亚驻阿富汗士兵犯下战争罪行的材料公开<ref name=":0" /><ref name="Xenophon2">{{Cite web|title=If moral courage matters, this whistleblower needs defending|url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/if-moral-courage-matters-this-whistleblower-needs-defending-20201116-p56ey4.html|date=2020-11-17|last=Xenophon|first=Nick|access-date=2020-11-19|website=The Age|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107231944/https://www.theage.com.au/national/if-moral-courage-matters-this-whistleblower-needs-defending-20201116-p56ey4.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2018年9月，麦克布莱德被捕<ref name="Wroe" />。2019年3月，他又被控四项罪名<ref name="ABCALumni">{{Cite web|title=ABC Alumni Limited Submission to Senate Standing committee On Environment and Communications’ References Committee: Inquiry into the adequacy of Commonwealth laws and frameworks covering the disclosure and reporting of sensitive and classified information|url=https://www.aph.gov.au/DocumentStore.ashx?id=23ecd67e-51eb-4e93-b055-83086647c857&subId=669151|date=29 August 2019|access-date=19 November 2020|archive-date=2022-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220522013424/https://www.aph.gov.au/DocumentStore.ashx?id=23ecd67e-51eb-4e93-b055-83086647c857&subId=669151}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=2019-06-13|title=Afghan Files whistleblower David McBride's trial delayed to protect state secrets|url=http://www.theguardian.com/law/2019/jun/13/afghan-files-whistleblower-david-mcbrides-trial-delayed-to-protect-state-secrets|access-date=10 November 2020|work=The Guardian|archive-date=2020-12-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201208184634/https://www.theguardian.com/law/2019/jun/13/afghan-files-whistleblower-david-mcbrides-trial-delayed-to-protect-state-secrets|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Burgess|first=Katie|date=9 November 2020|title=Afghanistan inquiry: Calls to drop prosecution of whistleblower David McBride|url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/7019615/afghanistan-inquiry-calls-to-drop-prosecution-of-whistleblower-david-mcbride/|access-date=19 November 2020|work=[[The_Canberra_Times|The Canberra Times]]|archive-date=2021-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112130015/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/7019615/afghanistan-inquiry-calls-to-drop-prosecution-of-whistleblower-david-mcbride/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Burgess|first=Katie|date=19 November 2020|title=The Afghanistan inquiry: what we know so far|url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/7017713/the-afghanistan-inquiry-what-we-know-so-far/|access-date=19 November 2020|work=The Canberra Times|archive-date=2020-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205145857/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/7017713/the-afghanistan-inquiry-what-we-know-so-far/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Knaus|first=Christopher|date=7 March 2019|title=Whistleblower charged with exposing alleged military misconduct 'not afraid to go to jail'|work=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/mar/07/whistleblower-charged-with-exposing-alleged-military-misconduct-not-afraid-to-go-to-jail|access-date=19 November 2020|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127110238/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/mar/07/whistleblower-charged-with-exposing-alleged-military-misconduct-not-afraid-to-go-to-jail|dead-url=no}}</ref>；2019年5月30日的听证会上，麦克布莱德拒绝认罪<ref name="ABCALumni" /><ref name="Maiden">{{cite news|last1=Maiden|first1=Samantha|title=Whistleblower behind ABC raid stands by Afghan leaks|url=https://thenewdaily.com.au/news/national/2019/06/05/abc-raid-david-mcbride/|accessdate=19 November 2020|work=The New Daily|date=5 June 2019|archive-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116215516/https://thenewdaily.com.au/news/national/2019/06/05/abc-raid-david-mcbride/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。截至2020年11月，尚未被审判<ref name=":0" />。 

